		<td><b>nesasm c-style defines?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Totally simple thing I'm sure I've missed, but is there a way to do c-style #defines for declaring constant values with nesasm? <br /><br />Thanks!<br />djcc

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Dwedit</b> [ Thu Jun 02, 2011 8:14 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Have you tried .equ or = ?
<br />It varies from assembler to assembler, but in many, you can use .equ or = to declare a label, such as
<br />
<br />MyVariable .equ $0123
<br />
<br />or
<br />
<br />MyVariable = $0123

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


